Defendant Quentin D Thurman in court with attorney Eryn M Menden.  Brian J. Juech appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court quashes warrant and reinstates bail.  State filed an amended information.  Defense acknowledges receipt of amended information and waives further reading.  Defense is prepared to enter a change of plea today.  Court conducts plea colloquy.  Defendant enters a plea of no contest to Count 1,  Court finds defendant guilty.  Cases 16CF47 and 17CF330 dismissed and read in to this matter.  Recommendations by the State.  Arguments by the State.  Statements by the Defendant.

The Court Orders the Following:
Withheld Sentence (Credit for 35 days if revoked)
Term of Probation: 1 Year - Probation may be transferred to Milwaukee County

Conditions of Probation:
-	Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;

Restitution: $1983.31   to be paid to Educators Credit Union as a condition of probation.

Costs: $253.00 to be paid as a condition of probation
 
DNA Surcharge: $200.00 to be paid as a condition of probation

DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 

Expunction is conditionally granted upon verification of completion of sentence, payment of all restitution/costs/fees, and no new law violations. If the Defendant violates any terms of his/her probation, or has any condition time imposed, the Court will deem that the conditions precedent necessary for the conditional grant of Expunction have not been met and therefore Expunction is denied. The defendant shall file a petition with the Court to verify the successful completion of the sentence.
